      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:4:21:8",
      "text": [
        " صَلَّى بِنَا أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) الْمَغْرِبَ فَقَرَأَ بِالْمُعَوِّذَتَيْنِ فِي الرَّكْعَتَيْنِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husayn, from Ibn Abu Najran, from Safwan Al Jammal who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> prayed Al Maghrib <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span> with us, so he<sup>asws</sup> recited with the <span class=\"iTxt\">Mawazatayn</span> (Chapters 113 & 114) during the two <span class=\"iTxt\">Rak’at</span>’ (<span class=\"iTxt\">Rak’at</span>s)."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from af-Husayn ibn abu Najran from Safwan al-Jammai who has said the foiiowing: “Abu ’Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, once led us in al-Maghrib Salah (prayer) and recited al- Ma’udhatayn in two Rak’at.” "
        ]
      }
